frameDefinitions: A Recipient starts off without the Theme in their possession, and then comes to possess it.
After a period in which the Agent has been working on a Goal, the Agent manages to attain it.
An Agent works on a Project so that it reaches a more advanced and desirable state.
An Asset is in a state where it is exposed to or otherwise liable to be affected by a Harmful_event, which may be metonymically evoked by reference to a Dangerous_entity.
This frame describes a Theme losing its autonomy and perhaps sustaining material damage as the result of a successful invasion on the behalf of a Conqueror.
The Creator creates a new entity, the Created_entity, possibly out of Components.
frameExamples: If you are a farmer, you are at <t>risk</t> for hearing loss caused by noise exposure in your work.
The Spaniards <t>conquered</t> the Incas with both the Cross and the arquebus
The Libyans were <t>generating</t> arms for export.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Recipient</fen> indicates the entity that ends up in possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that changes possession.
When the event occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> denotes where the Getting takes place.
The conscious entity, generally a person, that performs the intentional act that fulfills the <fen>Goal</fen>.
The state or action that the <fen>Agent</fen> has wished to participate in.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> achieves their <fen>Goal</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> achieves their <fen>Goal</fen>.
The object or idea that undergoes change due to the efforts of the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The individual that brings about the development of the <fen>Project</fen>.
The time at which the progress occurs.
The location at which the the <fen>Project</fen> progresses.
Something judged to be desirable or valuable which might be lost or damaged.
An action that may occur or a state which may hold which could result in the loss of or damage to the <fen>Asset</fen>.
A concrete or abstract entity which may come to cause the loss of, or damage to the <fen>Asset</fen> either due to its participation in a <fen>Harmful_event</fen>.
The time period during which the <fen>Asset</fen> enjoys  the specified level of security from a <fen>Harmful_event</fen>.

A particular location in which the <fen>Asset</fen> is secure. Frequently, it is to be inferred that the characteristics of the location protect the <fen>Asset</fen> from a potential <fen>Harmful_event</fen>.
The <fen>Conqueror</fen> is the entity that overtakes the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the land, government, and its people that is seized by the <fen>Conqueror</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Conqueror</fen> seizes the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Conqueror</fen> takes over the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The Creator creates a created entity.
This role identifies the entity that the Agent intentionally creates.
This role identifes the Time when an Agent intentionally creates a new entity.
This role identifies the place ehere the Agent intentionally creates the new entity.

not have enough military power.

Britain had an opportunity to conquer <fex>Europe</fex>.
China 's <fex>1997</fex> takeover would push over 10 per cent of the population out of the colony
